In [17]:
def forecastData(location,marla,newdf,lst_all_data):
  newdf1 = newdf.loc[newdf['Area_Marla'] == marla]
  if (len(newdf1['price'])>4):
    
    df = newdf1[['price']]

    df.reset_index( inplace=True)
    df = df.rename(columns={"date":"ds" , "price":"y"})

    m = Prophet(daily_seasonality=True )
    m.fit(df)

    future = m.make_future_dataframe(periods=365)
    future.tail()

    forecast = m.predict(future)
    forecast[['ds', 'yhat', 'yhat_lower', 'yhat_upper']].tail()
    forecast.head()

    fig1 = m.plot(forecast)

    fig2 = m.plot_components(forecast)

    plot_plotly(m, forecast)

    plot_components_plotly(m, forecast)
    
    # df['bathrooms']=newdf1['bathrooms']
    # df['bedrooms']=newdf1['bedrooms']
    # df['location']=[location for i in range(len(df['ds']))]
    # df['Area_Marla']=[marla for i in range(len(df['ds']))]

    forecast['location']=[location for i in range(len(forecast['ds']))]
    forecast['Area_Marla']=[marla for i in range(len(forecast['ds']))]
    
    #Median of bedrooms
    median_bedrooms =  int(math.floor(newdf1['bedrooms'].median()))
    #Median of bathrooms
    median_bathrooms =  int(math.floor(newdf1['bathrooms'].median()))
    lst_beds=list(newdf1['bedrooms'])
    lst_baths=list(newdf1['bathrooms'])

    msize=len(lst_beds)
    l_range=len(forecast['ds'])-msize
    for i in range(l_range):
      lst_beds.append(median_bedrooms)
      lst_baths.append(median_bathrooms)
    
    # forecast['bedrooms']=[median_bedrooms for i in range(len(forecast['ds']))]
    # forecast['bathrooms']=[median_bathrooms for i in range(len(forecast['ds']))]
    forecast['bedrooms']=lst_beds
    forecast['bathrooms']=lst_baths


    lst_all_data.append(forecast)

  return lst_all_data

def runMyFunc():
    dfn=dataX
    lst_locations=list(dfn['location'].unique())
    lst_locations
    lst_all_data=[]
    lst_all_rms=[]
    
    for loc in lst_locations:
        #Selecting only D-12/3, D-12 area values 
        newdf = dfn.loc[df['location'] == loc]
        #Now selecting onlt 4 marla houese 
        lst_area=list(newdf['Area_Marla'].unique())
        for area in lst_area:
            lst_all_data=forecastData(loc,area,newdf,lst_all_data)
#             if(rms>0):
            # lst_all_data.append(data)
            # lst_all_rms.append(rms)

    
    return lst_all_rms,lst_all_data
